column95:
text:"&lt;p&gt;You can download sample CSV files here for testing purposes. The datasets can be used in any software application compatible with CSV files. An easy tool to edit CSV files online is our &lt;a href=&quot;/csv-editor&quot;&gt;CSV Editor&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Five datasets are available:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#customers-dataset&quot;&gt;Customers&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;#download-customers-sample-csv-files&quot;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#people-dataset&quot;&gt;People&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;#download-people-sample-csv-files&quot;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#organizations-dataset&quot;&gt;Organizations&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;#download-organizations-sample-csv-files&quot;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#leads-dataset&quot;&gt;Leads&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;#download-leads-sample-csv-files&quot;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#products-dataset&quot;&gt;Products&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;#download-products-sample-csv-files&quot;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For each dataset

column97:
 from 100 to 2 million records. The first line contains the CSV headers. An index column is set on each file. Rows have an index value which is incremental and starts at 1 for the first data row.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All datasets are &lt;strong&gt;free&lt;/strong&gt; to download and play with. All the data is &lt;strong&gt;random&lt;/strong&gt; and those files must only be used for testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The script used to generate all those CSV files is open source and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/datablist/sample-csv-files&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;available on Github&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
